   <i> any presidential elections</i>  

06:15.441 --> 06:16.841
   <i> in more than ten years,</i>     

06:16.943 --> 06:19.644
<i>since President Mahmoud Abbas</i>   
<i>came to power.</i>                  

06:19.746 --> 06:22.179
     <i> And with polls showing</i>    
     <i> that nearly 70%</i>           

06:22.281 --> 06:24.381
  <i> of the population wanting</i>    
  <i> him out of office,</i>           

06:24.483 --> 06:27.117
    <i> the anger on the streets</i>   
    <i> is palpable.</i>               

06:27.219 --> 06:30.120
 (speaking in foreign language) 

06:56.215 --> 06:57.982
          Shihab-Eldin:         
      <i> Just down the street</i>     

06:58.084 --> 07:00.250
      <i> from Mahmoud Abbas'</i>      
      <i> presidential palace,</i>     

07:00.352 --> 07:04.221
<i>we found a group of protesters</i>  
<i>calling for him to step down.</i>   

07:05.825 --> 07:08.225
 (speaking in foreign language) 

07:38.524 --> 07:40.524
             Shihab-Eldin:      
       <i> A lot of the Palestinian</i>
            <i> youth tell us</i>      

07:40.627 --> 07:44.194
  that they see                 
  the Palestinian Authority     
  as a symbol of the occupation.

07:44.296 --> 07:45.830
                 Why would they 
                 be saying that?

07:45.932 --> 07:47.932
Well, the aspect of             
the Palestinian Authority       

07:48.034 --> 07:50.735
that's most unacceptable        
to Palestinians                 

07:50.837 --> 07:52.637
is its security                 
cooperation with Israel.        

07:52.739 --> 07:55.806
          Shihab-Eldin:         
      <i> That's because under</i>     
      <i> the Oslo Agreements</i>      

07:55.908 --> 08:00.144
 <i> the Palestinian Authority</i>     
 <i> security forces are charged</i>   
 <i> with maintaining the peace,</i>   

08:00.246 --> 08:03.580
    <i> which includes</i>             
    <i> suppressing protests.</i>      

08:03.683 --> 08:07.652
<i>But it's what the PA can't do</i>   
<i>that's angering</i>                 
<i>the Palestinians,</i>               

08:07.754 --> 08:10.187
   <i> which is their</i>              
   <i> inability to stop Israelis</i>  

08:10.289 --> 08:13.223
<i>from creating new settlements</i>   
<i>in the occupied West Bank.</i>      

08:13.325 --> 08:15.626
What has happened since 1967    

08:15.728 --> 08:20.430
is the establishment of         
communities of Israelis inside  
the occupied territories.       

08:20.533 --> 08:23.067
<i>Every place that a settler</i>      
<i>goes, the military goes.</i>        

08:23.169 --> 08:25.636
<i>Every place the military goes,</i>  
<i>restrictions against</i>            

08:25.738 --> 08:28.338
the native population,          
the Palestinians, follow.       

08:28.440 --> 08:32.376
This is why settlements         
are such an enormous factor     

08:32.477 --> 08:34.812
in the West Bank                
