     Right over there is        
     a Palestinian cemetery.    

11:52.211 --> 11:54.544
     If you look,               
     all of the tombstones      
     are written in Arabic.     

11:54.646 --> 11:58.849
  It's literally two feet away  
  from a street where           
  Palestinians can't come.      

12:02.154 --> 12:05.322
 <i> And even on the Palestinian</i>   
 <i> side back in H1,</i>              

12:05.424 --> 12:08.859
     <i> we could see how rigid</i>    
     <i> this divide was.</i>          

12:09.828 --> 12:12.062
 (speaking in foreign language) 

12:42.962 --> 12:44.828
         Shihab-Eldin:          
<i>As more and more kids grow up</i>   

12:44.931 --> 12:46.596
       <i> under the rules</i>         
       <i> of this agreement,</i>      

12:46.698 --> 12:52.303
    <i> it will only feed</i>          
    <i> into more violence</i>         
    <i> and a furthering divide.</i>   

12:52.405 --> 12:55.739
<i>Dr. Hanan Ashrawi was involved</i>  
<i>in the early negotiations</i>       

12:55.841 --> 12:57.174
       <i> of the Middle East</i>      
       <i> peace process,</i>          

12:57.276 --> 13:00.210
 <i> and a former member of</i>        
 <i> the Palestinian Authority.</i>    

13:00.313 --> 13:03.347
Young Palestinians              
taking to the streets           
and throwing rocks              

13:03.449 --> 13:06.450
say they're                     
not just disillusioned          
by the occupation,              

13:06.552 --> 13:09.486
they tell us                    
they're disillusioned           
by their own government.        

13:09.588 --> 13:12.756
 The Palestinian Authority      
is part of the occupation.      

13:12.858 --> 13:16.460
            We're not surprised 
           that the young people
            are disillusioned,  

13:16.562 --> 13:17.828
           <i> and they are angry.</i> 

13:17.930 --> 13:20.264
        <i> They're sending a clear</i>
        <i> message to the world.</i>  

13:20.366 --> 13:23.233
   The peace agenda,            
   the negotiated settlement,   

13:23.336 --> 13:25.135
          the two-state solution
          has not worked.       

13:25.237 --> 13:26.903
             The leadership     
             could not deliver. 

13:27.006 --> 13:29.440
It seems like                   
there's a bigger                
and bigger disconnect.          

13:29.541 --> 13:30.841
       There is a wide gap, yes.

13:30.943 --> 13:32.642
               These perceptions
               are cumulative.  

13:32.744 --> 13:35.012
         If you allow           
         your system to atrophy,

13:35.114 --> 13:36.913
            your leadership     
            to become geriatric,

13:37.016 --> 13:40.884
   <i> then of course you're going</i> 
   <i> to have a situation of total</i>
   <i> discontent and anger.</i>       

13:40.987 --> 13:44.754
           The only way forward 
           is through elections.

13:44.857 --> 13:46.991
       We need elections,       
       we need a new leadership,

13:47.093 --> 13:49.193
           and we need the youth
           to be part of this.  

13:49.295 --> 13:52.629
         Shihab-Eldin:          
<i>Until that happens, the youth</i>   
